OL,3,CFailing hospitals in England to be
OL,4,Cnamed and shamed in league tables
OL,6,FNHS England will undertake a "no holds
OL,7,Fbarred" review of its performance with
OL,8,Fthe aim of producing public league
OL,9,Ftables that rank NHS Trusts on a range
OL,10,Fof indicators such as finances,
OL,11,Fdelivery of services, patient access
OL,12,Fto care and competency of leadership.
OL,14,FUnder the government plans, these
OL,15,Ftables will be regularly updated and
OL,16,Fmanagers who persistently fail will be
OL,17,Fdenied pay rises or replaced.
OL,18,FTurnaround teams will be sent to
OL,19,Ftrusts that have big financial
OL,20,Fdeficits or are offering patients a
OL,21,Fpoor service.
